---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Policy Tracker"
  description="What the SaferAI Policy Tracker is, how it's produced, and how to contribute."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>About</h1>
    <p class="tagline">
      A clean reading tool for the weekly AI-policy digests produced by SaferAI.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="prose">
    <h2>What this is</h2>
    <p>
      The SaferAI Policy Tracker is a lightweight static site that collects the
      three digest streams our policy team produces each week: a legislative
      digest, a newsletter digest, and a paper-tracking digest. The goal is a
      calm, readable interface for researchers who want a single place to scan
      what moved in AI policy, what's on the radar, and what's worth reading
      this week.
    </p>

    <h2>How it's produced</h2>
    <p>
      Each digest is generated by a scheduled Claude Code routine that reads
      from the monitored sources listed on the <a href="sources">Sources</a>
      page, drafts a structured markdown file, and commits it to the repository
      under <code>content/YYYY-MM-DD/</code>. This site is then rebuilt from
      those markdown files — there is no database and no runtime rendering.
      Everything you see is static HTML generated at build time.
    </p>

    <h2>How to request a new source</h2>
    <p>
      If there's a newsletter, legislative feed, author, or venue you think we
      should be tracking, please <a href="#" rel="noopener">open an issue on
      GitHub</a> and tell us why. The policy team reviews source requests
      monthly.
    </p>

    <h2>Who maintains it</h2>
    <p>
      The tracker is maintained by the SaferAI policy team. For questions or
      collaboration, please reach out through the usual SaferAI channels or via
      the repository linked in the footer.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
